in national borders. Though strategies like full employment, mass education, and progressive taxation are not especially controversial, none of the BRICS have truly embraced them. Examining barriers to implementation, Elsenhans and Babones find that the main obstacle to such reforms is an absence of political will, stemming from closely guarded elite privilege under the current laws. BRICS or Bust? is a short, incisive read that underscores the need for demand-driven growth and why it has yet to be achieved.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 4aBRICS. 4aBrazil. 4aChina. 4aIndia. 4aRussia. 4aSouth Africa. 4aexchange rates. 4afull employment. 4amass incomes. 4amiddle-income trap. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Economic Development.2bisacsh1 aBabones, Salvatore, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360491940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503604919423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503604919.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles